BOJ’s Shirakawa Says Banking System in Japan Remains Healthy

-- B y   T o r u   F u j i o k a
-- 
2011-10-15T15:07:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-15/boj-s-shirakawa-says-banking-system-in-japan-remains-healthy.html
Bank of Japan  Governor Masaaki Shirakawa said the country’s banking system remains healthy.  Shirakawa spoke to reporters in Paris after a meeting with
Group of 20 finance chiefs and central bankers, where he said he
raised concerns about the strong yen.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Toru Fujioka in Tokyo at 
